<HL>
   Italy's 1st-Period Debt Narrows
</HL>
<DATE>
05/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   MILAN -- Italy's public-sector deficit narrowed to a
provisional 25.318 trillion lire ($20.85 billion) in the
first quarter of the year from a revised deficit of 30.307
trillion lire in the first three months of 1989, the Treasury
announced yesterday.
   The government deficit for the first quarter of 1989 was
revised upward from an original estimate of 29.746 trillion
lire.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Treasury said that tax revenue amounted to 70.955
trillion lire. Public sector spending totaled 79.037 trillion
lire, while Treasury operations resulted in a deficit of
17.236 trillion lire.
   The deficit was covered with the issuing of medium-term
and long-term government securities totaling 9.833 trillion
lire, debt issues placed abroad resulting in net revenue of
397 billion lire and other kinds of government debt totaling
15.088 trillion lire.
</TEXT>
